<title>USA: Audi sees return to profit in U.S. in '97.</title>
<headline>Audi sees return to profit in U.S. in '97.</headline>
<dateline>DETROIT 1997-01-07</dateline>
<text>
<p>German carmaker Audi AG expects to make a profit in its U.S. business in 1997 after breaking even in 1996, its U.S. chief Gerd Klauss said at the Detroit car show.</p>
<p>Audi, a subsidiary of Volkswagen AG, sold 27,379 cars in the U.S. in 1996, its highest sales since 1987 and up 51.1 percent from 1995 when it made a loss in the U.S., Klauss said late on Monday.</p>
<p>Audi was aiming for a 20 percent increase in sales in the U.S. in 1997, Klauss said.</p>
<p>He added Audi might be able to achieve annual sales of about 50,000 cars in the U.S. by the year 2000.</p>
